law.text:
Public higher education in Maryland should be based on the following principles:
The people of Maryland expect quality in all aspects of public higher education: teaching, research, and public service;
Public higher education should be accessible to all those who seek and qualify for admission;
Public higher education should provide a diversity of quality educational opportunities;
Adequate funding by the State is critical if public higher education is to achieve its goal;
The people of Maryland are entitled to efficient and effective management of public higher education; and
The people of Maryland are entitled to capable and creative leadership in public higher education.
